time
mKMRCT1 "All the delay stage delays" This value represents a maximum delay between the time the car goes from closed to open loop fuel target values. There are several other potential delays but setting this to 0 should override them. For performance applications to ensure that the ecu transitions to the fuel target as fast as possible upon wide open throttle, set to 0.
mTS14VZ Injector Open Time in Microseconds
mDTS "TS voltage compensation coefficient" This is the value in milliseconds that is added to the "injector latency 14V table for every 1v drop in voltage. IE: if latency at 14v is 2ms and the adder is 1ms then the latency at 13v would be 3ms.

mTCCLV This table is how the ecu calculates 100% load at x rpm. The values shown are 100% load calculated from the base fuel schedule milliseconds. This is important for proper automatic transmission shifting. It needs to be adjusted so that the ecu sees at or near 100% when wide open throttle to correctly shift the automatic transmission.
